00:19:52,270 --> 00:19:58,430
Speaker 1: The check-in time, the hotel officially states, is the time when all the rooms are ready for getting in no matter what.

264
00:19:59,311 --> 00:20:03,970
Speaker 1: So, depending on where your room is in the hotel, it's pretty much a crapshoot whether you can get in early or not.

265
00:20:04,010 --> 00:20:05,353
Speaker 0: Also, how early you arrive.

266
00:20:05,533 --> 00:20:13,770
Speaker 0: Like, we go to Otacon, we arrive Thursday morning, so we check in at, like, 11 AM, and they usually have some rooms ready and they just give them to us right away.

267
00:20:14,130 --> 00:20:14,199
Speaker 1: Yep.

268
00:20:14,750 --> 00:20:20,170
Speaker 0: And the earlier you check in, the more likely you'll be able to choose where your rooms are in the hotel if you have a preference or anything like that.

269
00:20:20,490 --> 00:20:22,910
Speaker 1: Yeah, if they didn't already decide that when you made your reservation.

270
